Welcome:
- This course is designed to help you get started building apps for mobile devices that run the Android operating system.
- We learn the following topics in this course:
  - history of Android
  - how to set up Android Studio and the Android SDK on your development computer
  - how to prepare both virtual and physical devices for testing.
  - how to create brand new Android Studio projects,
  - how to define an app's visual presentation with XML layout files and widgets,
  - how to control an app's behavior with Java code.
  - how to navigate between screens
  - how to present lists of data and images
  - how to support the enormous variety of screen sizes and pixel densities that we see in Android devices.
  - This course helps get started building apps for the ever expanding world of the Android operating system and
    application framework.
